   "source": [
    "# Scores\n",
    "\n",
    "Click the button below to run this notebook directly on Google Colab:\n",
    "\n",
    "[<img src=\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\" align=\"left\">](https://colab.research.google.com/github)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Introduction:\n",
    "\n",
    "This time you will create the data.\n",
    "\n",
    "***Exercise based on [Chris Albon](http://chrisalbon.com/) work, the credits belong to him.***\n",
    "\n",
    "### Step 1. Import the necessary libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 2. Create the DataFrame that should look like the one below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,\n    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }\n   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_data = {\n",
    "    'first_name': ['Jason', 'Molly', 'Tina', 'Jake', 'Amy'],\n",
    "    'last_name': ['Miller', 'Jacobson', 'Ali', 'Milner', 'Cooze'],\n",
    "    'age': [42, 52, 36, 24, 73],\n",
    "    'sex': [0, 1, 1, 0, 1],\n",
    "    'preTestScore': [4, 24, 31, 2, 3],\n",
    "    'postTestScore': [25, 94, 57, 62, 70]\n",
    "}\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(raw_data, columns = ['first_name', 'last_name', 'age', 'sex', 'preTestScore', 'postTestScore'])\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 3. Create a Scatterplot of preTestScore and postTestScore, where the size of each point is determined by age\n",
    "#### Ready to place the labels"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.scatter(df.preTestScore, df.postTestScore, s=df.age)\n",
    "plt.title(\"preTestScore vs postTestScore\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel('preTestScore')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('postTestScore')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Step 4. Create a Scatterplot of preTestScore and postTestScore.\n",
    "### This time the size should be 4.5 times the postTestScore and the color determined by sex"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.scatter(df.preTestScore, df.postTestScore, s=df.postTestScore * 4.5, c=df.sex)\n",
    "plt.title(\"preTestScore vs postTestScore\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel('preTestScore')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('postTestScore')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### BONUS: Create your own question and answer it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Question: Create a bar plot showing the preTestScore and postTestScore for each individual."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[['first_name', 'preTestScore', 'postTestScore']].set_index('first_name').plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.title('Comparison of Pre and Post Test Scores')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Scores')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('First Name')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
